<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="div1" xml:id="text" n="0">
  <head>Text in MEI</head>
  <p>This chapter describes methods for encoding textual content with MEI. Textual information on scores has several different uses, although some text is closer to music notation than other. For example tempo marks, directives an lyrics are directly functional to the notated music and are, therefore, described in other chapters (see for example <ptr target="#lyrics"/> and <ptr target="#textDirectives" />). This chapter, on the other hand, focuses on the text that accompanies the score, such as paratext (prefatory material, title pages, back matter, appendices, etc.), titles, prose, poetry, etc.</p> 
  <p>Most of the elements described here take inspiration from encoding formats that deal primarily with text, such as HTML and the Text Encoding Initiative (TEI). These elements are provided to encode relatively basic textual information. For deeper encoding of text, these Guidelines recommend to consider the use of other text-specific encoding formats.</p>
  <div type="div2" xml:id="textFrontandBack">
    <head>...</head>
    <p>...</p>
  </div>
  <div type="div2" xml:id="textStructure">
    <head>...</head>
    <p><!-- div, head --></p>
    <div type="div3" xml:id="textProse">
      <head>...</head>
      <p><!-- p, quote, list, item --></p>
    </div>
    <div type="div3" xml:id="textPoetry">
      <head>...</head>
      <p><!-- lg, l --></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

